# facet-xml

XML serialization and deserialization for Rust using the facet reflection framework.

## A Simple Example

Given this XML:

```xml
<name>Ella</name>
```

You can deserialize it into a struct:

```rust
# use facet::Facet;
# use facet_xml as xml;
#[derive(Facet, Debug)]
#[facet(rename = "name")]
struct Name {
    #[facet(xml::text)]
    value: String,
}
# let xml_str = "<name>Ella</name>";
# let name: Name = facet_xml::from_str(xml_str).unwrap();
# assert_eq!(name.value, "Ella");
```

The `#[facet(rename = "name")]` makes the struct match the `<name>` element, and `#[facet(xml::text)]` captures the text content inside.

## Attributes

```xml
<link href="/home">Home</link>
```

```rust
# use facet::Facet;
# use facet_xml as xml;
#[derive(Facet, Debug)]
#[facet(rename = "link")]
struct Link {
    #[facet(xml::attribute)]
    href: String,
    
    #[facet(xml::text)]
    text: String,
}
# let xml_str = r#"<link href="/home">Home</link>"#;
# let link: Link = facet_xml::from_str(xml_str).unwrap();
# assert_eq!(link.href, "/home");
# assert_eq!(link.text, "Home");
```
